# Vocabulary Growth

does NOT happen through:

```text id="m5v8qe"
memorization alone
```

Students learn vocabulary through:

```text id="q2m4qe"
context
+
discussion
+
repeated exposure
```

Students learn:

```text id="r9v1qe"
read
→ notice clues
→ infer meaning
→ confirm understanding
```

This develops:

* vocabulary
* reading fluency
* inference
* comprehension
* language flexibility

This becomes:

# Meaning Detective Thinking

Common misconceptions:

children may:

```text id="x7m3qe"
skip unknown words
```

or think:

```text id="u1v6qe"
one clue
always tells meaning
```

Research shows:

context clues help—

but readers must:

```text id="p8m2qe"
check meaning
carefully
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="k4v7qe"
meaning through evidence
```

